title: Quake hits mount rainier
author: Seattle Times Staffseattle Times News Services
text: MOUNT RAINIER - A moderate earthquake with an epicenter about nine miles west of Mount Rainier was recorded at 5:48 a.m. yesterday.     The University of Washington's seismology laboratory registered the quake at 4.1 on the Richter scale. Rumbling was felt as far south as Tacoma. A UW spokeswoman said the quake, about 22 miles south of Enumclaw, was similar to one that occurred in 1988.     There were no reports of injuries or significant damage
